---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "KitchenAid Appliance Repair Los Angeles | Same Day Service";
const description = "Expert KitchenAid appliance repair in Los Angeles. Certified technicians for refrigerators, ranges, dishwashers, stand mixers & more. Same-day service, genuine OEM parts, 90-day warranty. Call (626) 376-4458.";
const phone = "(626) 376-4458";
const phoneRaw = "6263764458";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "HomeAndConstructionBusiness",
  "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — KitchenAid Specialist",
  "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brand-kitchenaid-appliance-repair/",
  "telephone": "+16263764458",
  "address": {
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "addressLocality": "Los Angeles",
    "addressRegion": "CA",
    "postalCode": "90001",
    "addressCountry": "US"
  },
  "areaServed": ["Los Angeles County", "Orange County", "Ventura County"],
  "priceRange": "$$",
  "openingHours": "Mo-Sa 08:00-20:00",
  "hasOfferCatalog": {
    "@type": "OfferCatalog",
    "name": "KitchenAid Repair Services",
    "itemListElement": [
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"KitchenAid Refrigerator Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"KitchenAid Range Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"KitchenAid Dishwasher Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"KitchenAid Stand Mixer Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"KitchenAid Cooktop Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"KitchenAid Ice Maker Repair"}}
    ]
  }
}
</script>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does KitchenAid appliance repair cost in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Most KitchenAid repairs run $165–$580. Common fixes like a dishwasher door latch, igniter replacement, or ice maker valve are on the lower end. Control board work or sealed system repairs run higher. Diagnostic fee is $89, waived when you proceed. Written flat-rate estimate before any work begins."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you repair KitchenAid stand mixers?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. We repair KitchenAid stand mixers — Artisan, Professional 600, and Commercial series. Common issues: gear grease hardening (causes a grinding noise and speed inconsistency), worn carbon brushes on older models, and governor failure on tilt-head models. Parts availability is excellent — the mixer platform has barely changed since the 1960s."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Why does my KitchenAid ice maker keep failing in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "LA hard water (250–400 ppm) is the primary culprit. Mineral scale clogs the water inlet valve, coats the ice maker mold, and reduces water flow to the point where ice production stops or produces small, malformed cubes. We clear the scale, replace the inlet valve if it has seized, and recommend a filter change schedule matched to your actual water hardness."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is KitchenAid the same as Whirlpool?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes — KitchenAid has been part of Whirlpool Corporation since 1986. Many major appliances share the Whirlpool platform: the same control board families, similar sealed system designs, and overlapping parts. This is good news for repair: parts availability is excellent, and we carry a wide inventory that covers both brands."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How do I know if my KitchenAid appliance has been recalled?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "You can check at cpsc.gov using your model number. KitchenAid and Whirlpool have had several recalls over the years — particularly on dishwashers (fire risk from heating element) and some range models. We check recall status on every service call before beginning work."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you service KitchenAid Professional and Commercial-Style ranges?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. KitchenAid Professional Series and Commercial-Style ranges (KFGC and KFCC series) are among the most common premium ranges we service in LA. Common issues include igniter failure, control board faults, and oven temperature calibration. We carry OEM igniters and control boards for current models on the truck."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

<style>
  :root {
    --red: #C8102E;
    --black: #0a0a0a;
    --gray: #f5f5f5;
    --border: #e2e2e2;
    --text: #1a1a1a;
    --muted: #6b6b6b;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  body { font-family: 'Barlow', 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif; color: var(--text); }

  .top-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 8px 24px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; font-size: 13px; color: #fff; }
  .top-bar a { color: #fff; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }

  .hero { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px 64px; color: #fff; }
  .hero-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 420px; gap: 48px; align-items: center; }
  .hero-eyebrow { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .hero-title { font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 52px); font-weight: 900; line-height: 1.05; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .hero-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 540px; }
  .hero-cta-group { display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-primary { display: inline-block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .btn-secondary { display: inline-block; border: 1px solid #555; color: #ccc; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .hero-badge-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; }
  .hero-badge { background: #161616; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; padding: 16px 18px; }
  .badge-num { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--red); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .badge-label { font-size: 12px; color: #888; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }

  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 14px 24px; }
  .trust-bar-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
  .trust-item { color: #fff; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .trust-item::before { content: "✓ "; }

  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section-gray { background: var(--gray); }
  .section-black { background: var(--black); color: #fff; }
  .section-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section-num { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .section-title { font-size: clamp(24px, 3.5vw, 36px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .section-black .section-title { color: #fff; }
  .section-lead { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
  .section-black .section-lead { color: #999; }

  .services-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .service-card { background: #fff; padding: 28px 24px; }
  .service-icon { font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-name { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin-bottom: 10px; color: var(--text); }
  .service-desc { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-issues { font-size: 12px; color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .tip-block { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); background: #fff8f8; padding: 18px 20px; margin: 32px 0; max-width: 760px; }
  .tip-label { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .tip-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--text); }
  .tip-blue { border-color: #3a7bd5; background: #f0f7ff; }
  .tip-blue .tip-label { color: #3a7bd5; }
  .tip-yellow { border-color: #c8960a; background: #fffbf0; }
  .tip-yellow .tip-label { color: #c8960a; }

  .features-2col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 48px; align-items: start; }
  .features-list { list-style: none; }
  .features-list li { padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2a2a; font-size: 15px; color: #ccc; display: flex; gap: 12px; }
  .features-list li::before { content: "→"; color: var(--red); flex-shrink: 0; }

  .platform-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 24px; }
  .platform-table th { background: #1a1a1a; color: #fff; text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  .platform-table td { padding: 12px 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2a2a; font-size: 14px; color: #ccc; vertical-align: top; }
  .platform-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .brand-cell { font-weight: 700; color: var(--red); }

  .problems-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .problem-card { border: 1px solid var(--border); background: #fff; padding: 20px; }
  .problem-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; color: var(--text); }
  .problem-cause { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .problem-tag { display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; padding: 3px 8px; color: #fff; }
  .tag-common { background: var(--red); }
  .tag-la { background: #2a5ea5; }
  .tag-pro { background: #333; }

  .pricing-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 24px; }
  .pricing-table th { background: var(--text); color: #fff; text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  .pricing-table td { padding: 14px 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 14px; }
  .pricing-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .pricing-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--gray); }
  .price-range { font-weight: 700; color: var(--red); }

  .why-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 24px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .why-card { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); padding: 20px; background: #fff; }
  .why-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .why-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .why-desc { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }

  .reviews-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .review-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px; }
  .review-stars { color: var(--red); font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .review-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .review-author { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); }

  .repairs-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 32px; }
  .repair-item { background: #fff; padding: 24px; }
  .repair-appliance { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .repair-issue { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .repair-detail { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .repair-meta { margin-top: 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: #aaa; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .faq-list { margin-top: 32px; }
  .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px 0; }
  .faq-q { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .faq-a { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; }

  .nearby-grid { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .nearby-chip { background: var(--gray); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
  .nearby-chip:hover { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red); }

  .bottom-cta { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px; text-align: center; color: #fff; }
  .bottom-cta-title { font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .bottom-cta-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .bottom-cta-sub { font-size: 17px; color: #888; margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .cta-phone-large { display: inline-block; font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 42px); font-weight: 900; color: #fff; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 24px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--red); padding-bottom: 4px; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .hero-badge-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .features-2col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .trust-bar-inner { flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
  }
</style>

<!-- TOP BAR -->
<div class="top-bar">
  <span>Mon–Sat 8am–8pm · Los Angeles &amp; Southern California</span>
  <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`}>{phone}</a>
</div>

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">KitchenAid Appliance Repair — Los Angeles</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">
        KitchenAid Repair.<br/>
        <span>100 Years.</span><br/>
        One Call.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        From the original 1919 stand mixer to today's Commercial-Style ranges and counter-depth refrigerators — we repair everything KitchenAid makes. Same day, OEM parts, written estimate before we start. And yes, we fix the mixer.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-cta-group">
        <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="btn-primary">Call {phone}</a>
        <a href="/book/" class="btn-secondary">Book Online</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-badge-grid">
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">Same</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Day Service</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">OEM</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Parts Only</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">90-Day</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Warranty</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">$89</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Diagnostic Fee</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TRUST BAR -->
<div class="trust-bar">
  <div class="trust-bar-inner">
    <span class="trust-item">Licensed &amp; Insured · CSLB #1138898</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Factory-Certified Technicians</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Genuine KitchenAid OEM Parts</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Stand Mixer Specialists</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Flat-Rate Written Estimate</span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- 01 — ABOUT KITCHENAID -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">01 — About KitchenAid</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">From the 1919 Mixer to the Professional Series Range</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">
      KitchenAid started with a stand mixer in 1919 — still one of the most recognizable appliances ever made, still built in Greenville, Ohio, with a platform design that has barely changed in 60 years. By the 1980s they'd added dishwashers, ranges, refrigerators, and the full kitchen suite. In 1986, KitchenAid became part of Whirlpool Corporation, which is the most consequential fact for repair: under the hood, most KitchenAid major appliances share the Whirlpool platform.
    </p>
    <p class="section-lead">
      That platform overlap means excellent parts availability and deep diagnostic knowledge. We carry Whirlpool/KitchenAid control boards, igniters, ice maker components, and sealed-system parts on every truck — more than we can carry for any purely independent brand. When your KitchenAid refrigerator stops cooling or your Professional Series range has an igniter issue, we're usually in and out same day.
    </p>

    <div class="tip-block tip-blue">
      <div class="tip-label">🔩 The Whirlpool Platform Advantage</div>
      <div class="tip-text">KitchenAid, Whirlpool, Maytag, Amana, and JennAir all share overlapping component platforms. A KitchenAid KRFF507E French door refrigerator and a Whirlpool WRF535SMHZ use the same control board family, the same ice maker module, the same defrost heater design. This means we carry more compatible parts, diagnose faster, and complete more repairs in one visit than shops that only specialize in one brand at a time.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 — SERVICES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">02 — Services</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Every KitchenAid Appliance We Service</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">Same-day availability across Los Angeles County. We stock OEM KitchenAid and compatible Whirlpool-platform parts on every truck.</p>

    <div class="services-grid">
      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">❄️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Refrigerator Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">French door, side-by-side, bottom-freezer, built-in, counter-depth, and undercounter models. KitchenAid refrigerators share the Whirlpool sealed system, so compressor and sealed-system repairs are within our certified scope. Our techs are EPA-certified for refrigerant work.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: not cooling · ice maker failure · water dispenser clogged · control board · defrost drain blocked · compressor · temperature fluctuation · door gasket</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔥</div>
        <div class="service-name">Range &amp; Oven Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">All KitchenAid range series — Professional (KFGC/KFCC), Architect, Commercial-Style, standard slide-in and freestanding. Gas, dual-fuel, and induction. Commercial-Style ranges in particular are common in high-end LA kitchens and have specific igniter and valve configurations we know well.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: igniter not sparking · oven not heating · temperature calibration · control board · bake/broil element · door hinge · self-clean lock failure</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🍽️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Dishwasher Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">All KitchenAid dishwasher series including the top-control and front-control models. KitchenAid dishwashers share the Whirlpool platform — parts are excellent and failures are predictable. We also check recall status before beginning any dishwasher work.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: not draining · not cleaning · door latch failure · control board · water inlet valve · pump motor · spray arm blocked · heating element</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🌀</div>
        <div class="service-name">Washer &amp; Dryer Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">KitchenAid front-load and top-load washers, electric and gas dryers. The KitchenAid laundry platform is shared with Whirlpool and Maytag — extensive parts inventory means fast, single-visit repairs in most cases.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: not spinning · not draining · door latch · bearing failure · thermal fuse · heating element · control board · dryer not heating · drum belt</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔆</div>
        <div class="service-name">Cooktop Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">Gas, electric, induction, and downdraft cooktops. KitchenAid induction cooktops in particular require a technician familiar with the inverter and element design — different failure modes than gas or standard electric.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: igniter failure (gas) · surface element failure (electric) · induction not responding · downdraft motor · control board · burner won't light</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🥣</div>
        <div class="service-name">Stand Mixer Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">KitchenAid Artisan, Professional 600, Professional 5, and Commercial series. The stand mixer platform is one of the most repairable appliances made — the design has been stable for decades, parts are excellent, and most failures are mechanical rather than electronic. We repair the gear assembly, governor, and worm gear grease that most shops won't touch.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: grinding noise (gear grease hardened) · speed inconsistency (governor) · stops under load (worm gear) · attachment hub damaged · leaking oil</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block tip-yellow" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">⚠️ Recall Check — Every Dishwasher Service Call</div>
      <div class="tip-text">KitchenAid and Whirlpool have issued several product recalls over the years — most notably dishwasher recalls related to heating element fire risk. We check CPSC recall status for your model before beginning any dishwasher repair. If your appliance is under an active recall, we'll tell you before touching it. You can also check yourself at cpsc.gov with your model number.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 — PLATFORM KNOWLEDGE -->
<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">03 — Platform Knowledge</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">The Whirlpool Family — Why It Matters for Your Repair</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">Understanding KitchenAid's position in the Whirlpool brand family isn't just trivia — it directly affects parts availability, diagnosis speed, and repair cost.</p>

    <table class="platform-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Brand</th>
          <th>Positioning</th>
          <th>Shared Platform With KitchenAid</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="brand-cell">KitchenAid</td>
          <td>Premium / Professional-style</td>
          <td>Core platform for refrigerators, dishwashers, washers, dryers, ranges</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="brand-cell">Whirlpool</td>
          <td>Mid-range flagship</td>
          <td>Same control board families, same sealed systems, same ice maker designs on many models</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="brand-cell">Maytag</td>
          <td>Durability-focused</td>
          <td>Washer/dryer platforms largely shared; some refrigerator components cross-compatible</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="brand-cell">JennAir</td>
          <td>Luxury/Professional</td>
          <td>Recent JennAir redesigns share the KitchenAid Professional platform in key areas</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="brand-cell">Amana</td>
          <td>Value</td>
          <td>Basic refrigerator and washer platforms overlap; simpler components, same diagnostic tools</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div style="margin-top:40px">
      <div class="features-2col">
