<!-- 04 — COMMON PROBLEMS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">04 — Common Problems</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Most Common KitchenAid Failures in Los Angeles</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">KitchenAid appliances fail in well-documented patterns. LA's hard water and high entertainment/cooking frequency creates its own signature failure mix.</p>

    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">❄️ Ice Maker Not Making Ice</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Water inlet valve clogged with mineral scale (LA hard water) or failed outright. Secondary: ice maker module failure, clogged water filter, frozen fill tube. We test the inlet valve first — it's the culprit in over 60% of LA ice maker calls — before pulling the module.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-la">LA Hard Water</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔥 Gas Range Igniter Clicking Constantly</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Moisture or food debris on the igniter tip — the ceramic igniter is cracked or contaminated. On Commercial-Style KitchenAid ranges, the dual-stack burner igniters are particularly susceptible to grease contamination from high-output cooking. Cleaning sometimes resolves it; cracked igniters need OEM replacement.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🥣 Mixer Grinding / Speed Loss</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Gear grease hardening — the most common KitchenAid mixer failure. The original grease used from the factory becomes brittle over 10–15 years, losing its lubricating properties and causing the planetary gear assembly to grind under load. A complete gear regrease resolves this in almost every case.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🍽️ Dishwasher Not Cleaning Top Rack</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Upper spray arm clogged (hard water deposits block nozzle holes) or low water pressure reaching the upper arm due to a partially failed wash pump. We test water pressure at the upper arm port, clear the spray arm, and inspect the pump motor before recommending parts.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-la">LA Hard Water</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌡️ Oven Temperature Off</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Bake element failure or temperature sensor (oven thermostat) out of calibration. KitchenAid wall ovens and ranges allow user temperature calibration in the settings — we check if this was accidentally adjusted before pulling components. Bake element failure is confirmed with a resistance test.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔆 Induction Cooktop Not Responding</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Induction element inverter failure or a cracked glass surface. KitchenAid induction cooktops are finicky about pot compatibility — we verify the cookware first. Actual inverter failure shows as a single zone dead while others work. Control board failure affects all zones.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-pro">Professional Series</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

