    <h2 class="section-title">KitchenAid Repair FAQ</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How much does KitchenAid appliance repair cost in Los Angeles?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Most KitchenAid repairs run $165–$580. Common fixes like a dishwasher door latch, igniter replacement, or ice maker inlet valve are $165–$320. Control board work or sealed system repairs run higher. Diagnostic fee is $89, waived when you proceed. Written flat-rate estimate before any work begins.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Do you repair KitchenAid stand mixers?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes — including the Artisan, Professional 600, and Commercial series. Most common repair: gear grease hardening, which causes grinding and power loss under load. We do a complete gear assembly disassembly, clean, and regrease with modern synthetic grease. Typically 2 hours, same day. Most shops decline mixer work — we specialize in it.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Is KitchenAid the same as Whirlpool?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes — KitchenAid has been part of Whirlpool Corporation since 1986. Many major appliances share the same control board families, sealed systems, ice maker designs, and washer/dryer platforms. This means better parts availability and faster repairs: we carry Whirlpool/KitchenAid platform parts on every truck.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Why does my KitchenAid ice maker keep failing?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">LA hard water (250–400 ppm) is the primary culprit in most zip codes. Mineral scale clogs the water inlet valve and ice mold heater within 2–4 years without adequate filtration. We replace the inlet valve with an OEM part, flush the water line, and set a filter replacement schedule matched to your actual local water hardness.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How do I check if my KitchenAid appliance has been recalled?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Visit cpsc.gov and search by model number. KitchenAid and Whirlpool have had several recalls — most notably dishwasher heating element fire hazards. We check recall status on every service call before beginning any work on dishwashers and ranges.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Do you service KitchenAid Professional and Commercial-Style ranges?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes — KitchenAid Professional Series (KFGC, KFCC) and Commercial-Style ranges are among the most common premium ranges we service in LA. They use specific OEM igniters and valve configurations. We keep these parts stocked. Common issues: igniter failure, control board, and oven temperature calibration.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Do you offer preventive maintenance for KitchenAid appliances?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. We recommend annual maintenance for KitchenAid refrigerators (coil cleaning, door gasket check, water filter replacement), dishwashers (spray arm flush, heating element check, recall verification), and ranges (igniter inspection, oven temperature calibration). In LA's hard-water environment, annual maintenance prevents most of the failures we're called for.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
